          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRAEP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " In-hospital Neutron Irradiator (IHNI)",
                "is a Miniature Neutron Source reactor (MNSR) of pool-",
                "tank type."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The measured thermal neutron (<0.5 eV) flux",
                "density is 1.92E9 /cm2/s at the exit aperture of the",
                "thermal neutron beam, and the diameter of the exit is",
                "12 cm. The share of thermal neutrons is about 87%.",
                "The contribution of epi-cadmium neutron induced",
                "fission to the absolute fission yields has been",
                "estimated to be about 0.25%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The axial grid ionization chamber with a",
                "silicon nitride entrance window of 100 nm thickness",
                "was tested and calibrated with a 252Cf spontaneous",
                "fission source. The intrinsic energy resolution for",
                "1.27 MeV/u 63Cu particles is measured to be 450 keV",
                " (FWHM)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The time resolution was determined with two",
                "microchannel plate (MCP) timing detectors to be 157ps",
                " (FWHM) for 241Am radiation source, implying that the",
                "intrinsic time resolution is about 110ps (FWHM) for a",
                "single timing detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "E-v method"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The flight path length is 100.45 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.902
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The UO2 target was electroplated",
                "on to an aluminium backing and had a thickness of",
                "about 500 ug/cm2. The effective diameter of this",
                "target is 1.6 cm. The neutron beam is collimated by",
                "the boron-doping polyethylene and cadmium into a",
                "quasi-parallel beam with a diameter of 5 cm, and the",
                "entire uranium target was enclosed by neutron beams."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The energy loss as a function of fragment mass given",
                "through the Geant4 event-by-event computation method."
              ]
            }
          ],
